This is the way I see it---and he may too.
Seeing as you installed the engine, he could very well back pedal out of
this undesirable situation by simply saying--you dropped it---or you did
this, or did that--- and he therefore has zero liability---
However, if he openly admitted to you he missed the hole--he may offer
some assistance---

Did you inquire as too what he would be able to do for you, after the
first hole patch job----or after it fell out?
I didn't see anything mentioned about what you had said to him about
this mysterious hole in the case

Ask first, worry about recourse later,

Was this a running engine out of your bus prior to you having it
rebuilt, or something you picked up elsewhere--at a bargain deal?

If it was a running engine in your bus--I was just wondering myself
where the hole came from--

Later,

