said he would fix and then I could come back and pick it up. Well when I
went back to pick it up he said he had some "BAD NEWS FOR ME". He told
me that there was a hole in the block and that he did not notice it when
he was rebuilding it. He said that he would put some high temp epoxy on
it and it would be fine....I thought oh great this is going to be a
disaster. So he puts the stuff on it then runs the engine to see if it
leaked it did not so called me and told me to pick it up and that all
was well. Anyway about 3000 miles later (while driving up to go back to
school) the engine starts to leak oil pretty bad. So I take it back to
him and tell him whats up he looks at it the next day and then tells me
that it is the hole and that engine is useless. I said ok took the bus
and brought it home not saying anything about him not finding the hole
